title: MIT designed a fleet of autonomous boats that could help reduce car traffic

organizations.name: computer science and artificial intelligence laboratory

text: These 3D printed, self-driving boats could help ease traffic in cities with waterways 1 Hour Ago Researchers at MITâ€™s Computer Science and Artificial Intelligence Laboratory (CSAIL) and the Senseable City Lab in the Department of Urban Studies and Planning (DUSP), have designed a fleet of affordable 3D printed, autonomous boats. The goal is to transport people and goods in cities with waterways to reduce road traffic.
